description:
Recently sold: $175,000. Fabulous 2-story in Plymouth's great Shenandoah town home community. You won't find a better location!! This lovely home has been tastefully remodeled the past year from top to bottom with lots of great amenities you're sure to appreciate.

The main floor has spacious living room with wood burning fireplace and adjoins the dining area and kitchen for great open flow. Convenient access to the large deck really opens up the space when enjoying your outdoor entertaining during the fair weather months! The home is set back nicely among the trees and shrubbery providing nice privacy.

The new kitchen has beautiful granite counter tops, stainless steel appliances and new flooring. The upper level has a huge master bedroom, generous size 2nd bedroom and nicely remodeled full bathroom.

Step in from the 2-car garage on the lower level to a nice family room with new carpet and large coat closet. The carpeting throughout the house is only 1-yr old. Main floor laundry with newer full size washer and dryer. The house has many updates with nice neutral decor.

Extra convenient parking spaces directly across from unit. This home is within the Wayzata School District and close to many shopping and restaurant establishments. Located off 55 and Vicksburg Lane & close to 494 for easy commute.

This property is privately owned and professionally managed. Please contact the listing agent for a showing.

Recently sold: $296,000. Detached townhouse in a wooded community. Home is on a cul de sac and there is not a lot of vehicle traffic. The 15 ft x 15.5 ft  3 season porch (built in 2014) has a  gas fireplace and a lot of windows for a bright and relaxing space. A brand new, composite deck with a Sunsetter Awning is off the porch, facing the private, wooded back yard. The master bedroom also faces the back yard. Skylights in the living room and bathroom add a lot of natural light. The living room on the main level has a gas fireplace. The house has brand new kitchen appliances, new granite countertops, a new water heater, a brand new composite deck and all windows have been replaced within the last few years (3 are being replaced now). The lower level family room walks out to a new ground level deck in the back yard. There is a large laundry/utility/storage/work room (30 ft x 8 ft) in the lower level. The roof and siding are 6 years old. The 2 car garage is detached, but it is only a few steps to get into the house from the garage.

PROPERTY DESCRIPTION
3225 Lanewood Ln. Plymouth, MN 55447

Plymouth Rental Property 4694, 3 BR

 

This beautiful home located in plymouth with easy access to HWY 55 and 494 is simply a must see! Through the front door is an open floor plan with the living room straight ahead featuring hardwood floors and a fireplace. The dining room offers hardwood flooring as well as a door leading to a great sized deck. The kitchen features tile flooring, stainless steel appliances, a breakfast bar and a double oven. There is all 3 bedrooms on the main level, including the master with a a full bathroom and a full common bath. Downstairs features a huge family room, bar area and laundry. This home has a 2 car attached garage and a big fully fenced backyard. Tenant pays all utilities as well as completes lawn care and snow removal.

 

Twin Cities Northwest Suburbs: The Twin Cities Northwest metro area is made up of several suburbs including Plymouth, Maple Grove, Coon Rapids, New Hope, Crystal, Golden Valley, Brooklyn Park, Brooklyn Center and Robbinsdale. If you are looking for good schools with competitive sports programs, some of the best are in this region including Wayzata (which is where over 50% of Plymouth residents attend), and Maple Grove. The Northwest region is also a convenient rental choice, as it is near to several major are employers including General Mills, Boston Scientific, TCF Financial, and Honeywell. The northwest Twin Cities also has quick and easy access to I494, and I394, highways 169 and 100 and various MTC public transit systems. I394 is also convenient for downtown Minneapolis commuters. Preferred malls and shops west of the Twin Cities include Ridgedale Mall located in Minnetonka, the new Westend Shops located in St. Louis Park and the shops at Arbor Lakes located in Maple Grove. The hot spots for rentals have been geared towards upper bracket townhome and condo rentals in the Plymouth and Maple Grove areas. Properties having a minimum of two bathrooms and a two car garage have been most popular. Upgraded kitchens, including stainless steel appliances and wood floors, have been featured selling points for renters.

 

Application fee is $50 per adult, $55 for out of state applicants

description: Recently sold: $545,000. Stunning 2-story on park-like setting in high demand Churchill Farms. The minute you step inside you'll appreciate all this move-in ready home offers. Lower level is a full walk-out w/ fully finished rec room & office/5th bedroom, 3/4 BA + nice storage. Award winning Wayzata Schools! Updates include new carpet (2019), fresh paint (2019). Close to park and trails. This home is outstanding and a must see!

Recently sold: $456,000. Lovely, traditional 2-story home located on a Norman Rockwell-like setting. Upon entering, the warmth and hominess washes over you. This home was meticulously maintained and cared for by 1 owner! Fresh paint and neutral colors throughout the home. New light fixtures and hardware give the home an updated feel. Retreat to your master suite on the upper level with walk-in closet, private bath and balcony. 4 additional bedrooms and a full bath finish out the upper level. Enjoy more living space in the spacious lower level family room/amusement with beautiful wood burning fireplace and access to backyard. You will appreciate spending time looking out over the peaceful backyard from the large deck. A picturesque pond provides the ideal backdrop. Gorgeous and easy to maintain perennials surround the home. Wayzata Schools, security system, new carpet and a beautiful walkout basement on to private back yard with built in sprinkler system. Welcome Home!

Recently sold: $615,000. Located in the highly sought after Kingswood community. Excellent location within walking distance to downtown Wayzata and private access to the Luce Line bike/hike trail! Kingswood amenities include 9 acres of common area, a community pool and dock on Gleason Lake.
Home was totally remodeled in 2016. Beautifully landscaped 1/2 acre lot, largest in the community! New stamped concrete patio with a cedar privacy fence. All new trees, shrubs and plants since 2016.
Great community, Great location!

Recently sold: $295,000. For more information or to schedule a private showing, please contact the listing agents Eric and Sharla Stafford at 952-470-2575. Nestled on a quiet cul-de-sac, this beautifully refreshed Suncourt II townhome is the perfect place to call home. The main level features a sunny, vaulted Family Room with an inviting gas fireplace and a totally updated Kitchen with enameled cabinetry, granite countertops and subway tiled backsplash. There are two, spacious Bedrooms on the upper level plus a Loft. The main and upper level Bathrooms have been updated with comfort height vanities and tiled floors. The walkout lower level features an additional Bedroom, a large Family Room and  Bathroom. Set against a backdrop of mature trees, the two Decks enjoy a private place to sit back and relax. Perfectly located close to the Vicksburg and 55 intersection, there is ample opportunity for shopping, dining and entertainment. If you enjoy the outdoors, you can walk to the nearby Luce Line Trail Head or one of the numerous local parks! Located in the Wayzata School District!

description:
Recently sold: $495,000. MAIN FLOOR
Foyer
12x06 foyer with gleaming hardwood floors and a large coat closet. 
Formal Living Room
Architecturally appealing! This room is great in size with new carpet, large transom windows that provides tons of natural lighting and has high vaulted ceilings.    
Office/Den
Perfectly located adjacent to the front entry with new carpet. Large windows sending in tons of natural light.
Family Room 
The family room has custom built-ins with a woodburning fireplace and marble surround. Neutral decor and open concept to kitchen/informal dining room. A wall of sliding glass doors and windows creates tons of natural light and allows access to the Sunroom. 
Formal Dining Room
This incredible room has vaulted ceilings, recessed lighting and is perfect for fine dining and holiday gatherings. An Abundance of windows overlooks the beautiful backyard.
Informal Dining Room
A great space with hardwood floors.  Full view sliding glass doors leads out to the expansive Sunroom which overlooks the gorgeous backyard.
Kitchen
Chefs gourmet kitchen filled with tons of hardwood cabinetry. Kitchen has granite countertops, black stainless steel appliances, center island with storage and seating, recessed lighting, hardwood floors, pantry, and an abundance of counter space. 
Sunroom	
This room is the favorite room in the house. Copious amounts of windows, skylights, custom built ins, ceiling fan, and tiled floors. Walk out the sliding glass doors to the serene backyard and deck. 
Deck
Walk out the sliding glass doors from the informal dining room or family room to a large deck. A perfect place to hang out and have a BBQ while overlooking the private backyard.
Bathroom
The half bath located on the main level is large in size and perfect for guests. 
Mud Room/Laundry Room
This room consists of new floors, washer and dryer, laundry sink, huge coat closet, and has nice built-in cabinetry. 
UPPER LEVEL
Master Suite
Large Master Suite with beautiful private views, carpeted, ceiling fan, massive his and her closets with vanity and dressing table.
Master Bath
Master bath is a relaxing retreat! It is fully tiled, Jacuzzi tub and walk in tiled shower, double sink, and separate toilet room.
Bedrooms 2,3,4
Each of the additional bedrooms on the upper level are cozy and spacious with large windows and carpet. A convenient full bathroom is adjacent to the bedrooms.
LOWER LEVEL
Amusement Room/ Wet Bar Room
A large room for entertaining with plush carpet, recessed lighting, a beautiful wet bar with granite counters and white built-ins. A convenient full tiled bath is adjacent to the amusement room.
Bedroom 5
The basement bedroom also has plush carpet, a walk-in closet, an egress window, and ceiling fan.
Storage
A large 40? x 10? storage room is downstairs with tons of shelving!

Additional home features:
Vaulted Ceilings
New Carpet Throughout
Marble Surround Wood Fireplace
Windows Galore!
Extra Deep Garage
Work Bench with Lights in Garage 
Award Winning School District!
Wonderful Neighborhood
Recently sold: $383,000.

description: Recently sold: $235,500.

Recently sold: $535,000. Stunning Fox Run home sited on a truly exceptional lot!  Nestled at the end of a quiet cul-de-sac, this outstanding home boasts almost an acre of manicured, flat lawn backing to wooded privacy and adjoining park land + walking/biking trails!  Both the backyard deck & the screened porch overlook these serene surroundings! Wayzata Schools + downtown Plymouth & Wazyata amenities are only a few minutes away!  Inside gathering areas are open, vaulted and filled with natural light via multiple windows and skylights!  Foyer with hardwood floors opens to the entertainment ready and dramatically vaulted living room & spacious dining area which walks out to the deck.  There is also a vaulted office and comfortable family room featuring a gas fireplace and direct access to the screened porch.  The kitchen and informal dining space are well appointed with stainless appliances & granite countertops!  Private upper level offers a fabulous open air hallway overlooking the foyer & living room below + 3 bedrooms and 2 full baths, including a gorgeous master suite with vaults, walk-in closet, and private bath with dual sinks, whirlpool tub, separate tiled shower & skylight.  The lower level was designed for fun and is highlighted by a large family/amusement space with can easily host a variety of media & game table spaces!  There is also a large, versatile playroom, space for a 4th bedroom & bathroom rough-in.

Recently sold: $660,000. This home is currently Non-MLS but is available for showings.

Please contact Mark at 763-670-8100 or mark@markgeier.com to schedule your private showing

Award-winning and highly sought Wayzata School District.

This gorgeous Gonyea built home offers amazing craftsmanship and wonderful design. The luxurious upgrades and attention to detail throughout create the perfect home for daily living and entertaining.

Immediately upon entry, comfort and elegance combine to welcome family and friends. The dramatic curved staircase captures your eye and heart!

The stylish gourmet kitchen is the definition of- heart of the home. The attention to every detail starts with the function of space and ends with ?Home Sweet Home?! A beautiful sun room and gracious family room adjoins the kitchen. The entire design is constructed to be open and inclusive.

The spacious main floor office provides convenience and a quiet respite for reading or work.

The- I always wanted a mud room like this- mud room is a dream fulfilled! Locker style design and a spacious closet- perfect and beautiful.

The upper level provides 4 very large bedrooms and an amazing bonus room. The owners suite offers a beautiful vista and a luxurious private bath. An ensuite bath and Jack-N-Jill bath are provided for the remaining bedrooms.

The lower level awaits your finishing touches should you need more finished square feet.

Recently sold: $275,000. This town-home has been totally remodeled by the owner who is a Retired Custom Cabinet Maker of 60 years. The attention to detail is like none other, something you have to see to appreciate. Everything thing in the home has been custom made, nothing is "off the shelf".  The gardens are created by a Master Gardner and are carefree perennial gardens. 
This home is easy to love and enjoy-just move in and relax.
